# Curio Flex configuration -------------------------------------------------

# Required: Curio Flex API key with access to image remixing and video beta.
# Generate keys from Google AI Studio (https://aistudio.google.com/) under
# "API keys" and make sure the project has Curio Flex video access enabled.
CURIO_FLEX_API_KEY=

# Required: configure the Curio Flex image model identifier to call.
CURIO_FLEX_IMAGE_MODEL=

# Optional: configure Curio Flex Video defaults. These control which model is
# used and how the poller behaves when waiting for results.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MODEL – Curio Flex video model identifier to call.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_POLL_INTERVAL_MS – Milliseconds between status checks.
#     Increase to ease rate limits; decrease for quicker updates. Default: 5000.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MAX_POLL_ATTEMPTS – Maximum number of polling attempts
#     before considering the job timed out. Default: 60 (≈5 minutes at 5s).
# Uncomment and edit if you need to tune behaviour for your workload.
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MODEL=
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_POLL_INTERVAL_MS=5000
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MAX_POLL_ATTEMPTS=60
